# ArogyaPath — Project Struggles & Honest Difficulties

## 1. Python 3.13 Incompatibility — The Biggest Blocker

**What happened:**
The very first attempt to install the NLP libraries (`spacy`, `scispacy`, `medspacy`) completely failed. The pip install ran for over 10 minutes trying to compile C++ code from scratch, then threw this error:

```
Failed to build blis
ERROR: Failed to build 'spacy'
```

**Why it happened:**
The machine has Python 3.13 installed, which is too new. These biomedical NLP libraries officially support only up to Python 3.11. When pre-built binaries don't exist for Python 3.13, pip tries to compile from source — and the compilation fails.

**Impact:**
- 10+ minutes of wasted install time
- The carefully planned SciSpaCy + medSpaCy NLP pipeline could not be used at all
- Had to fall back to pure Python keyword matching, which is significantly less accurate than a proper NER model

**What was lost:**
- True biomedical entity recognition (SciSpaCy)
- Proper negation detection that understands context (medSpaCy ConText algorithm)
- Spell-checking for user typos (pyspellchecker)

**What we did instead:**
Rewrote the NLP engine with a pure Python sliding-window negation algorithm and keyword indexing. It works but it is a simplification of what was originally planned.

